This program is a Go port of FreeCCR, a physics-based color-negative film-scan
converter:

    FreeCCR — https://github.com/toonoumi/FreeCCR
    Copyright (C) Halo Imagery and the FreeCCR authors
    Licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0)

FreeCCR-go is a derivative work: its conversion and color-adjustment pipeline
(negative inversion, working-space windowing, the adjustment chain, reference/
auto normalization, constants, and staging) is a language port of FreeCCR's
src/core/ccr_processor.py. Fidelity to the original is verified numerically
(see ref/AB.md).

Because the original is licensed under the AGPL-3.0, this port is likewise
licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License, version 3 or (at your
option) any later version. See the LICENSE file for the full text.

