Third-party components:
  - RAW decoding uses libraw (dual-licensed LGPL-2.1 / CDDL-1.0;
    https://www.libraw.org), linked via cgo when built with `-tags libraw`.
    The distributed macOS .app bundles libraw and its dependencies as dynamic
    libraries in Contents/Frameworks. libraw remains a separate dynamic library
    (not statically linked), so it can be replaced by the user as required by
    LGPL-2.1 §6. The corresponding license texts ship inside the bundle at
    Contents/Resources/licenses. When building from source, install libraw
    separately (e.g. `brew install libraw`).
  - libraw's own dependencies, also bundled in the distributed macOS .app:
      * Little CMS 2 (lcms2) ....... MIT license
      * libjpeg-turbo .............. BSD-style / IJG license
      * LLVM OpenMP runtime (libomp)  Apache-2.0 with LLVM exception
  - Go standard library and golang.org/x/image (BSD-3-Clause).
